Class VertexQueryFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tinkerpop.blueprints.util.DefaultQuery
      • com.tinkerpop.blueprints.util.DefaultVertexQuery
        • com.thinkaurelius.faunus.formats.VertexQueryFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Query, com.tinkerpop.blueprints.VertexQuery

    public class VertexQueryFilter
extends com.tinkerpop.blueprints.util.DefaultVertexQuery
    A filtering mechanism for, if possible, only getting particular aspects of a vertex from the graph. A minimum, the filtering is done on the Hadoop side of the computation. Makes use of VertexQuery from Blueprints to express such constraints.
    Author:
    Marko A. Rodriguez (marko@thinkaurelius.com), Matthias Broecheler (me@matthiasb.com)
